
Transfer files from one ec2 instance to another ec2 instance



sudo apt-get update

sudo apt-get install -y openssh-server

sudo service ssh restart

sudo which sshpass

sudo apt-get install sshpass

sudo apt-get install -y vim

To add users like,

--->$ sudo adduser main
-->here it will ask password..setup it.
-->to setup permissions like, /home/user.
-->$ sudo chmod 777 -R /home/user.

--->$ sudo vim /etc/sudoers
-->here to give full permissions like root level.

--->$ sudo vim /etc/ssh/sshd_config
--># Change to no to disable tunnelled clear text passwords
PasswordAuthentication no --> yes

-->Now to install jdk by using the below command.

--->$ sudo wget --no-cookies --no-check-certificate --header "Cookie: oraclelicense=accept-securebackup-cookie" "http://download.oracle.com/otn-pub/java/jdk/8u181-b13/96a7b8442fe848ef90c96a2fad6ed6d1/jdk-8u181-linux-x64.tar.gz" -O jdk-8-linux-x64.tar.gz

-->Then extract it by putting proper directory. And in .bashrc to set this path.

--->Now to install tomcat.
-->$ sudo wget http://www-us.apache.org/dist/tomcat/tomcat-8/v8.5.32/bin/apache-tomcat-8.5.32.tar.gz

-->Then extract it.

--->Now to install jenkins.war file.
---> wget http://mirrors.jenkins.io/war-stable/2.89.2/jenkins.war



